        "my-exit-survey": {
            "kind": "exp-lookit-exit-survey",
            "debriefing": {
                "title": "Thank you!",
                "blocks": [
                    {
                        "text": "Debrief",
                        "listblocks": [
                            {
                                "text": "In this activity, your child heard about a school called Sunny School and a club that a student named Ro made. Ro only allowed kids with short hair to be in the club. Your child answered some questions about Ro's rule: was it okay or not okay? Did they think the rule was really about short hair, or was it made to exclude girls? This study investigated how children think about rules that disproportionately impact a particular social group (known as 'disparate impact' rules). Your child may have seen one girl with short hair included in the club, or heard a justification for the rule. We were curious to see how these manipulations might impact children's perceptions of the rule." 
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "In these questions there were no right or wrong answers - nobody could know for sure who Ro wanted to play with, for example! But we ask kids to guess anyway, because we're curious about their intuition. This helps us learn more about the factors that impact perception of disparate impact rules."
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "Thank you again for your participation. You and your child are helping us understand how children think about different kinds of discrimination. You can find more of our lab's work at <a href='https://elc-lab-ucsd.com/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>on our website</a>. If you'd like to learn more about disparate impact rules, check out <a href='https://digitalcommons.wcl.american.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1095&context=facsch_lawrev' target='_blank' rel='noopener'> this article</a>!"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "Your $3 gift card will arrive within 7 days.",
                        "text": "Please contact elclab-coord@ucsd.edu if you have any issues accessing your gift card."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
